  "prompt": "Why did Ian Mckellen have emotional breakdowns when on set on the Hobbit?",
  "response": "Ian McKellen experienced emotional breakdowns on the set of \"The Hobbit\" largely due to the combination of the demanding filming schedule, the pressures of working in a heavily CGI-driven environment, and the challenges associated with age. Filming for \"The Hobbit\" was particularly intensive and prolonged, which took its toll on him physically and emotionally. \n\nAdditionally, McKellen has mentioned in interviews that he struggled with feeling isolated on set, especially when much of the work involved acting against green screens or imagining CGI creatures that were not present. This could lead to a sense of disconnection from the material and his fellow cast members.\n\nMoreover, the stress of being on a high-profile project and the expectations of fans added to the emotional burden. McKellen's candid discussions about his experiences highlight the often-overlooked emotional and mental challenges actors can face, especially in complex filming environments.",
